      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}} and {{sea-salt-fine}} until the mix looks like coarse breadcrumbs with pea-sized butter pieces visible. Add the {{water}} a tablespoon at a time, stirring with a knife, until the dough just comes together. Divide in two (one slightly larger for the base), wrap flat, and chill an hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Filling, assembly",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the pitted {{cherries}} with the second {{caster-sugar}}, {{cornflour}}, juice of the {{lemon}} and {{almond-extract}}. Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Roll the larger pastry disc to a 30 cm round and line the pie dish. Tip the filling in, doming slightly in the centre. Roll the second disc and lay over the top (or cut into strips and weave a lattice, see ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "vent strategy",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99aetk0000j4v450zkr7lw"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "). Seal the edges and crimp. If using a full top, cut five short slashes from the centre out as steam vents.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, two stages",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the top with the beaten {{eggs}} and scatter with {{demerara-sugar}}. Set the pie on a tray to catch drips. Bake at 200°C fan for 20 minutes, then drop to 180°C fan for another 30 to 35 minutes; the pastry should be deep gold and the filling should bubble visibly through the vents. Cool 30 minutes before slicing; the filling sets as it cools.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
